      "date": "2014-07-28 21:43:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Verified+1 Code-Review+1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nThis has fixed the problem that I was seeing in sanity test_17m and test_17o on my local test system.  However, it reports:\n\n LustreError: 4727:0:(obd_mount_server.c:1167:server_register_target())\n   testfs-MDT0000: error registering with the MGS: rc = -108 (not fatal)\n Lustre: Evicted from MGS (at MGC192.168.20.154@tcp_0) after server\n   handle changed from 0xd701f8441df892cd to 0xd701f8441df8af9f\n\nevery time.  It would be good to quiet those error messages as part of this patch, since a \"not fatal\" error shouldn't be printed on the console.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "18e0bbac92d456ac1dc6158dd53710624ebc2deb",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-07-28 23:14:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nI pushed http://review.whamcloud.com/11258 which is this patch plus some console message cleanup to reduce noise during reconnection, added a comment block, etc. so please check if that patch is ready before landing this one.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
